rlOspfv3.name: rlOspfv3
rlOspfv3.description: The private MIB module definition for Multi Instance OSPF V3 for IPv6 MIB.

RlRouterID.name: RlRouterID
RlRouterID.description: A 32-bit, unsigned integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the value of one of the router's IPv4 host addresses if IPv4 is configured on the router.
RlRouterID.reference: OSPF for IPv6, Appendix C.1, Global Parameters

RlLsID.name: RlLsID
RlLsID.description: A unique 32-bit identifier of the piece of the routing domain that is being described by a link state advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the Link State ID (LSID) has no addressing semantics.
RlLsID.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.4, Link State ID

RlOspfv3FastHelloMultiplierRange.name: RlOspfv3FastHelloMultiplierRange
RlOspfv3FastHelloMultiplierRange.description: The range of hello multipliers that determine how often Fast Hellos are exchanged.

RlOspfv3UpToRefreshInterval.name: RlOspfv3UpToRefreshInterval
RlOspfv3UpToRefreshInterval.description: The values configurable for variables bounded by the Refresh Interval.

RlOspfv3RestartHelperStatus.name: RlOspfv3RestartHelperStatus
RlOspfv3RestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a hitless restart helper for a neighbor.

RlOspfv3RestartExitReason.name: RlOspfv3RestartExitReason
RlOspfv3RestartExitReason.description: The reason for exiting an attempted graceful restart.

RlOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTC.name: RlOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTC
RlOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTC.description: The values one might be able to configure for variables bounded by the Refresh Interval.
RlOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTC.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix B, Architectural Constants

rlOspfv3Instance.name: rlOspfv3Instance
rlOspfv3Instance.description: Selected OSPFv3 Process ID. Additional key value for old fashion usage of OSPF standard MIB to support multi OSPF instance.

rlOspfv3GeneralGroupEntry.name: rlOspfv3GeneralGroupEntry
rlOspfv3GeneralGroupEntry.description: Information describing the configured global parame- ters to the Router OSPFv3 Process.

rlOspfv3ProcessId.name: rlOspfv3ProcessId
rlOspfv3ProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPFv3 process.

rlOspfv3RouterId.name: rlOspfv3RouterId
rlOspfv3RouterId.reference: OSPF for IPv6, Appendix C.1, Global Parameters
rlOspfv3RouterId.description: A 32-bit unsigned integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the 32-bit unsigned integer representation of one of the router's IPv4 interface addresses (if IPv4 is configured on the router). This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3AdminStatus.name: rlOspfv3AdminStatus
rlOspfv3AdminStatus.description: The administrative status of OSPFv3 in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the OSPFv3 Process is active on at least one interface; 'disabled' disables it on all interfaces. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3VersionNumber.name: rlOspfv3VersionNumber
rlOspfv3VersionNumber.description: The version number of OSPF for IPv6 is 3.

rlOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.name: rlOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus
rlOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 3, Splitting the AS into Areas
rlOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to denote whether this router is an area border router. The value of this object is true (1) when the router is an area border router.

rlOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.name: rlOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus
rlOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 3.3, Classification of routers
rlOspfv3ASBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is configured as an Autonomous System border router. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount.name: rlOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount
rlOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount.description: The number of AS-scope (e.g., AS-External) link state advertisements in the link state database.

rlOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum.name: rlOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum
rlOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the LS checksums of the AS-scoped link state advertisements contained in the link state database. This sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database or to compare the link state database of two routers.

rlOspfv3OriginateNewLsas.name: rlOspfv3OriginateNewLsas
rlOspfv3OriginateNewLsas.description: The number of new link state advertisements that have been originated. This number is incremented each time the router originates a new LSA. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of ospfv3DiscontinuityTime.

rlOspfv3RxNewLsas.name: rlOspfv3RxNewLsas
rlOspfv3RxNewLsas.description: The number of link state advertisements received that are determined to be new instantiations. This number does not include newer instantiations of self-originated link state advertisements. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of ospfv3DiscontinuityTime.

rlOspfv3ExtLsaCount.name: rlOspfv3ExtLsaCount
rlOspfv3ExtLsaCount.description: The number of External (LS type 0x4005) in the link state database.

rlOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.name: rlOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit
rlOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.description: The maximum number of non-default AS-external-LSA entries that can be stored in the link state database. If the value is -1, then there is no limit. When the number of non-default AS-external-LSAs in a router's link state database reaches ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit, the router enters Overflow state. The router never holds more than ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit non-default AS-external-LSAs in its database. ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit MUST be set identically in all routers attached to the OSPFv3 backbone and/or any regular OSPFv3 area (i.e., OSPFv3 stub areas and not-so-stubby-areas (NSSAs) are excluded). This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval.name: rlOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval
rlOspfv3ExitOverflowInterval.description: The number of seconds that, after entering Overflow state, a router will attempt to leave Overflow state. This allows the router to again originate non-default, AS-External-LSAs. When set to 0, the router will not leave Overflow state until restarted. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3DemandExtensions.name: rlOspfv3DemandExtensions
rlOspfv3DemandExtensions.reference: OSPF Version 2; Extending OSPF to Support Demand Circuits
rlOspfv3DemandExtensions.description: The router's support for demand circuits. The value of this object is true (1) when demand circuits are supported. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.name: rlOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth
rlOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3, Router interface parameters
rlOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.description: Reference bandwidth in kilobits per second for calculating default interface metrics. The default value is 100,000 KBPS (100 MBPS). This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3RestartSupport.name: rlOspfv3RestartSupport
rlOspfv3RestartSupport.reference: Graceful OSPF Restart, Appendix B.1, Global Parameters (Minimum subset)
rlOspfv3RestartSupport.description: The router's support for OSPF graceful restart. Options include no restart support, only planned restarts, or both planned and unplanned restarts. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3RestartInterval.name: rlOspfv3RestartInterval
rlOspfv3RestartInterval.reference: Graceful OSPF Restart, Appendix B.1, Global Parameters (Minimum subset)
rlOspfv3RestartInterval.description: Configured OSPF graceful restart timeout interval. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3RestartStrictLsaChecking.name: rlOspfv3RestartStrictLsaChecking
rlOspfv3RestartStrictLsaChecking.reference: Graceful OSPF Restart, Appendix B.2, Global Parameters (Optional)
rlOspfv3RestartStrictLsaChecking.description: Indicates if strict LSA checking is enabled for graceful restart. A value of true (1) indicates that strict LSA checking is enabled. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3RestartStatus.name: rlOspfv3RestartStatus
rlOspfv3RestartStatus.description: The current status of OSPF graceful restart capability.

rlOspfv3RestartAge.name: rlOspfv3RestartAge
rlOspfv3RestartAge.description: Remaining time in the current OSPF graceful restart interval.

rlOspfv3RestartExitReason.name: rlOspfv3RestartExitReason
rlOspfv3RestartExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at a graceful restart. none: no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress: a restart attempt is currently underway. completed: the last restart completed successfully. timedOut: the last restart timed out. topologyChanged: the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.

rlOspfv3NotificationEnable.name: rlOspfv3NotificationEnable
rlOspfv3NotificationEnable.description: This object provides a coarse level of control over the generation of OSPFv3 notifications. If this object is set to true (1), then it enables the generation of OSPFv3 notifications. If it is set to false (2), these notifications are not generated. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3StubRouterSupport.name: rlOspfv3StubRouterSupport
rlOspfv3StubRouterSupport.description: The router's support for stub router functionality. An object value of true (1) indicates that stub router functionality is supported.

rlOspfv3StubRouterAdvertisement.name: rlOspfv3StubRouterAdvertisement
rlOspfv3StubRouterAdvertisement.reference: OSPF Stub Router Advertisement, Section 2, Proposed Solution
rlOspfv3StubRouterAdvertisement.description: This object controls the advertisement of stub LSAs by the router. The value doNotAdvertise (1) will result in the advertisement of standard LSAs and is the default value. This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime.name: rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime
rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which any one of this MIB's counters suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re-initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

rlOspfv3RestartTime.name: rlOspfv3RestartTime
rlOspfv3RestartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which the ospfv3RestartExitReason was updated.

rlOspfv3OperStatus.name: rlOspfv3OperStatus
rlOspfv3OperStatus.description: The current operational state of the OSPF in the router.

rlOspfv3RowStatus.name: rlOspfv3RowStatus
rlOspfv3RowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

rlOspfv3LogAdjacencyChanges.name: rlOspfv3LogAdjacencyChanges
rlOspfv3LogAdjacencyChanges.description: Configure the router to send a syslog message when an OSPF neighbor goes up or down. detail sends a syslog message for each state change, not just when a neighbor goes up or down

rlOspfv3PassiveInterface.name: rlOspfv3PassiveInterface
rlOspfv3PassiveInterface.description: A flag to note whether to disable sending OSPF routing updates on all OSPF IP interfaces.

rlOspfv3DefaultMetric.name: rlOspfv3DefaultMetric
rlOspfv3DefaultMetric.description: A default metric helps solve the problem of redistributing routes with incompatible metrics. Whenever metrics do not convert, using a default metric provides a reasonable substitute and enables the redistribution to proceed.

rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixNum.name: rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixNum
rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixNum.description: Specifies the maximum number of IP prefixes that can be redistributed into OSPF.

rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixThreshold.name: rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixThreshold
rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixThreshold.description: Threshold value, as a percentage, at which a warning message should be generated.

rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixWarningOnly.name: rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixWarningOnly
rlOspfv3MaximumRedistPrefixWarningOnly.description: Causes a warning message to be logged when the number of prefixes defined by the maximum argumenthas been exceeded. Additional redistribution is not prevented.

rlOspfv3NextRouterId.name: rlOspfv3NextRouterId
rlOspfv3NextRouterId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the of router in the Autonomous System after restart. By convention, to ensure uniqueness, this should default to the value of one of the router's IP interface addresses.

rlOspfv3RouterIdType.name: rlOspfv3RouterIdType
rlOspfv3RouterIdType.description: Type of router identifier - default value or manually set by user.

rlOspfv3NextRouterIdType.name: rlOspfv3NextRouterIdType
rlOspfv3NextRouterIdType.description: Type of router identifier after restart - default value or manually set by user.

rlOspfv3ASBdrRtrActualStatus.name: rlOspfv3ASBdrRtrActualStatus
rlOspfv3ASBdrRtrActualStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is an Autonomous System Border Router. note: rlOspfASBdrRtrStatus field is the configuration and this filed is the actual ASBR status

rlOspfv3CalcMaxDelay.name: rlOspfv3CalcMaxDelay
rlOspfv3CalcMaxDelay.description: The maximum delay before the Routing Table is recalculated following a change to the Link State Database. (Recalculation is delayed to reduce the frequency of recalculations of the Routing Table). This parameter has units of milliseconds. A value of 0 indicates that a routing calculation will immediately follow an update to the database.

rlOspfv3RteMaxEqCostPaths.name: rlOspfv3RteMaxEqCostPaths
rlOspfv3RteMaxEqCostPaths.description: The maximum number of equal cost paths that are stored for each destination in the Routing Table.

rlOspfv3AreaTable.name: rlOspfv3AreaTable
rlOspfv3AreaTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 6, The Area Data Structure
rlOspfv3AreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas. The interfaces and virtual links are configured as part of these areas. Area 0, by definition, is the backbone area.

rlOspfv3AreaEntry.name: rlOspfv3AreaEntry
rlOspfv3AreaEntry.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of one of the router's attached areas. The information in this table is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the a change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3AreaProcessId.name: rlOspfv3AreaProcessId
rlOspfv3AreaProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3AreaId.name: rlOspfv3AreaId
rlOspfv3AreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2, Area parameters
rlOspfv3AreaId.description: A 32-bit unsigned integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.

rlOspfv3AreaImportAsExtern.name: rlOspfv3AreaImportAsExtern
rlOspfv3AreaImportAsExtern.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2, Area parameters
rlOspfv3AreaImportAsExtern.description: Indicates whether an area is a stub area, NSSA, or standard area. AS-scope LSAs are not imported into stub areas or NSSAs. NSSAs import AS-External data as NSSA LSAs that have Area-scope.

rlOspfv3AreaSpfRuns.name: rlOspfv3AreaSpfRuns
rlOspfv3AreaSpfRuns.description: The number of times that the intra-area route table has been calculated using this area's link state database. This is typically done using Dijkstra's algorithm. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime.

rlOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount.name: rlOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount
rlOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount.description: The total number of area border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each Shortest Path First (SPF) pass.

rlOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount.name: rlOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount
rlOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount.description: The total number of Autonomous System border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF pass.

rlOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount.name: rlOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount
rlOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Area-scope link state advertisements in this area's link state database.

rlOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum.name: rlOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum
rlOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Area-scope link state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this area's link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database or to compare the link state database of two routers.

rlOspfv3AreaSummary.name: rlOspfv3AreaSummary
rlOspfv3AreaSummary.description: The variable rlOspfv3AreaSummary controls the import of Inter-Area LSAs into stub and NSSA areas. It has no effect on other areas. If it is noAreaSummary, the router will neither originate nor propagate Inter-Area LSAs into the stub or NSSA area. It will only advertise a default route. If it is sendAreaSummary, the router will both summarize and propagate Inter-Area LSAs.

rlOspfv3AreaRowStatus.name: rlOspfv3AreaRowStatus
rlOspfv3AreaRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction, and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

rlOspfv3AreaStubMetric.name: rlOspfv3AreaStubMetric
rlOspfv3AreaStubMetric.description: The metric value advertised for the default route into stub and NSSA areas. By default, this equals the least metric among the interfaces to other areas.

rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole.name: rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole
rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole.description: Indicates an NSSA border router's policy to perform NSSA translation of NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs.

rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState.name: rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState
rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState.description: Indicates if and how an NSSA border router is performing NSSA translation of NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs. When this object is set to 'enabled', the NSSA border router's rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole has been set to 'always'. When this object is set to 'elected', a candidate NSSA border router is translating NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs. When this object is set to 'disabled', a candidate NSSA Border router is NOT translating NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs.

rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInterval.name: rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInterval
rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInterval.description: The stability interval defined as the number of seconds after an elected translator determines its services are no longer required that it should continue to perform its translation duties.

rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents.name: rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents
rlOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents.description: Indicates the number of Translator state changes that have occurred since the last start-up of the OSPFv3 routing process. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime.

rlOspfv3AreaStubMetricType.name: rlOspfv3AreaStubMetricType
rlOspfv3AreaStubMetricType.description: This variable assigns the type of metric advertised as a default route.

rlOspfv3AreaTEEnabled.name: rlOspfv3AreaTEEnabled
rlOspfv3AreaTEEnabled.description: Indicates whether or not traffic engineering is enabled in the area. The object is set to the value true (1) to enable traffic engineering. Traffic engineering is disabled by default.

rlOspfv3AreaAdminStat.name: rlOspfv3AreaAdminStat
rlOspfv3AreaAdminStat.description: The OSPF Area's administrative status. The value formed on the area, and the in- terfaces associated with the area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the area is external to OSPF.

rlOspfv3AreaOperStatus.name: rlOspfv3AreaOperStatus
rlOspfv3AreaOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the OSPF Area.

rlOspfv3AreaFilterPrefixListIn.name: rlOspfv3AreaFilterPrefixListIn
rlOspfv3AreaFilterPrefixListIn.description: The prefix list is applied to prefixes advertised to the specified area from other areas.

rlOspfv3AreaFilterPrefixListOut.name: rlOspfv3AreaFilterPrefixListOut
rlOspfv3AreaFilterPrefixListOut.description: The prefix list is applied to prefixes advertised out of the specified area to other areas.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbTable.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbTable
rlOspfv3AsLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's AS-scope link state database (LSDB). The LSDB contains the AS-scope link state advertisements from throughout the areas that the device is attached to.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbEntry
rlOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.description: A single AS-scope link state advertisement.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbProcessId.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbProcessId
rlOspfv3AsLsdbProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbType.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbType
rlOspfv3AsLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. AS-scope LSAs not recognized by the router may be stored in the database.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId
rlOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1, Global parameters
rlOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbLsid
rlOspfv3AsLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS type-specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbSequence
rlOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6, LS sequence number
rlOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number, the more recent the advertisement.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbAge.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbAge
rlOspfv3AsLsdbAge.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.1, LS age; Extending OSPF to Support Demand Circuits, Section 2.2, The LS age field.
rlOspfv3AsLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds. The high-order bit of the LS age field is considered the DoNotAge bit for support of on-demand circuits.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum
rlOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement
rlOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire link state advertisement, including its header.

rlOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown.name: rlOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown
rlOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown.description: The value true (1) indicates that the LSA type is recognized by this router.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbTable
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Area-scope LSDB. The LSDB contains the Area-scope link state advertisements from throughout the area that the device is attached to.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.description: A single Area-scope link state advertisement.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbProcessId.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbProcessId
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2, Area parameters
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.description: The 32-bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbType.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbType
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. Area-scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1, Global parameters
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS type-specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6, LS sequence number
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number, the more recent the advertisement.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAge
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.1, LS age; Extending OSPF to Support Demand Circuits, Section 2.2, The LS age field.
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds. The high-order bit of the LS age field is considered the DoNotAge bit for support of on-demand circuits.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire link state advertisement, including its header.

rlOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown.name: rlOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown
rlOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown.description: The value true (1) indicates that the LSA type is recognized by this router.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbTable
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Link-scope LSDB for non-virtual interfaces. The LSDB contains the Link-scope link state advertisements from the interfaces that the device is attached to.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.description: A single Link-scope link state advertisement.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbProcessId.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbProcessId
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.description: The identifier of the link from which the LSA was received.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId.description: The identifier of the interface instance from which the LSA was received.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbType.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbType
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. Link-scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1, Global parameters
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS type-specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics. However, in OSPFv3 the Link State ID always contains the flooding scope of the LSA.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6, LS sequence number
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number, the more recent the advertisement.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbAge
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.1, LS age; Extending OSPF to Support Demand Circuits, Section 2.2, The LS age field.
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds. The high-order bit of the LS age field is considered the DoNotAge bit for support of on-demand circuits.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire link state advertisement, including its header.

rlOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown.name: rlOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown
rlOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown.description: The value true (1) indicates that the LSA type is recognized by this router.

rlOspfv3HostTable.name: rlOspfv3HostTable
rlOspfv3HostTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.7, Host route parameters
rlOspfv3HostTable.description: The Host/Metric Table indicates what hosts are directly attached to the router and their corresponding metrics.

rlOspfv3HostEntry.name: rlOspfv3HostEntry
rlOspfv3HostEntry.description: A metric to be advertised when a given host is reachable. The information in this table is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3HostProcessId.name: rlOspfv3HostProcessId
rlOspfv3HostProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3HostAddressType.name: rlOspfv3HostAddressType
rlOspfv3HostAddressType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.7, Host route parameters
rlOspfv3HostAddressType.description: The address type of rlOspfv3HostAddress. Only IPv6 global address type is expected.

rlOspfv3HostAddress.name: rlOspfv3HostAddress
rlOspfv3HostAddress.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.7, Host route parameters
rlOspfv3HostAddress.description: The IPv6 address of the host. Must be an IPv6 global address.

rlOspfv3HostMetric.name: rlOspfv3HostMetric
rlOspfv3HostMetric.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.7, Host route parameters

rlOspfv3HostRowStatus.name: rlOspfv3HostRowStatus
rlOspfv3HostRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction, and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

rlOspfv3HostAreaID.name: rlOspfv3HostAreaID
rlOspfv3HostAreaID.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2, Area parameters
rlOspfv3HostAreaID.description: The Area the host entry is to be found within. By default, the area for the subsuming OSPFv3 interface, or Area 0 if there is no subsuming interface.

rlOspfv3IfTable.name: rlOspfv3IfTable
rlOspfv3IfTable.reference: OSPF for IPv6, Appendix C.3, Router Interface Parameters
rlOspfv3IfTable.description: The OSPFv3 Interface Table describes the interfaces from the viewpoint of OSPFv3.

rlOspfv3IfEntry.name: rlOspfv3IfEntry
rlOspfv3IfEntry.description: The OSPFv3 Interface Entry describes one interface from the viewpoint of OSPFv3. The information in this table is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3IfProcessId.name: rlOspfv3IfProcessId
rlOspfv3IfProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3IfIndex.name: rlOspfv3IfIndex
rlOspfv3IfIndex.description: The interface index of this OSPFv3 interface. It corresponds to the interface index of the IPv6 interface on which OSPFv3 is configured.

rlOspfv3IfInstId.name: rlOspfv3IfInstId
rlOspfv3IfInstId.description: Enables multiple interface instances of OSPFv3 to be run over a single link. Each interface instance would be assigned a separate ID. This ID has local link significance only.

rlOspfv3IfAreaId.name: rlOspfv3IfAreaId
rlOspfv3IfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.

rlOspfv3IfAdminStatus.name: rlOspfv3IfAdminStatus
rlOspfv3IfAdminStatus.description: The OSPFv3 interface's administrative status. The value formed on the interface; the interface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPFv3. Note that a value of 'disabled' for the object rlOspfv3AdminStatus will override a value of 'enabled' for the interface.

rlOspfv3IfRtrPriority.name: rlOspfv3IfRtrPriority
rlOspfv3IfRtrPriority.description: The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated-router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligible to become the Designated Router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their Router ID as a tie breaker.

rlOspfv3IfTransitDelay.name: rlOspfv3IfTransitDelay
rlOspfv3IfTransitDelay.reference: OSPF for IPv6, Appendix C.3, Router Interface Parameters.
rlOspfv3IfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a Link State Update packet over this interface. LSAs contained in the update packet must have their age incremented by this amount before transmission. This value should take into account the transmission and propagation delays of the interface.

rlOspfv3IfRetransInterval.name: rlOspfv3IfRetransInterval
rlOspfv3IfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link state advertisement retransmissions for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and Link State Request packets.

rlOspfv3IfHelloInterval.name: rlOspfv3IfHelloInterval
rlOspfv3IfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

rlOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval.name: rlOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval
rlOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before its neighbors declare the router down on the interface. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

rlOspfv3IfPollInterval.name: rlOspfv3IfPollInterval
rlOspfv3IfPollInterval.description: The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive, non-broadcast multi-access neighbor.

rlOspfv3IfState.name: rlOspfv3IfState
rlOspfv3IfState.description: The OSPFv3 interface state. An interface may be in standby state if there are multiple interfaces on the link and another interface is active. The interface may be in Down state if the underlying IPv6 interface is down or if the admin status is 'disabled' either globally or for the interface.

rlOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter.name: rlOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter
rlOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter.description: The Router ID of the Designated Router.

rlOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter.name: rlOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter
rlOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter.description: The Router ID of the Backup Designated Router.

rlOspfv3IfEvents.name: rlOspfv3IfEvents
rlOspfv3IfEvents.description: The number of times this OSPFv3 interface has changed its state or an error has occurred. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime.

rlOspfv3IfRowStatus.name: rlOspfv3IfRowStatus
rlOspfv3IfRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction, and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

rlOspfv3IfDemand.name: rlOspfv3IfDemand
rlOspfv3IfDemand.description: Indicates whether Demand OSPFv3 procedures (Hello suppression to FULL neighbors and setting the DoNotAge flag on propagated LSAs) should be performed on this interface.

rlOspfv3IfMetricValue.name: rlOspfv3IfMetricValue
rlOspfv3IfMetricValue.description: The metric assigned to this interface. The default value of the metric is 'Reference Bandwidth / ifSpeed'. The value of the reference bandwidth can be set in the rlOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth object.

rlOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount.name: rlOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount
rlOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Link-scope link state advertisements in this link's link state database.

rlOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum.name: rlOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum
rlOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Link-scope link state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this link's link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database or to compare the link state database of two routers.

rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe.name: rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe
rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbe.description: Indicates whether or not neighbor probing is enabled to determine whether or not the neighbor is inactive. Neighbor probing is disabled by default.

rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetransLimit.name: rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetransLimit
rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeRetransLimit.description: The number of consecutive LSA retransmissions before the neighbor is deemed inactive and the neighbor adjacency is brought down.

rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval.name: rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval
rlOspfv3IfDemandNbrProbeInterval.description: Defines how often the neighbor will be probed.

rlOspfv3IfTEDisabled.name: rlOspfv3IfTEDisabled
rlOspfv3IfTEDisabled.description: Indicates whether or not traffic engineering is disabled on the interface when traffic engineering is enabled in the area where the interface is attached. The object is set to the value true (1) to disable traffic engineering on the interface. Traffic engineering is enabled by default on the interface when traffic engineering is enabled in the area where the interface is attached.

rlOspfv3IfLinkLSASuppression.name: rlOspfv3IfLinkLSASuppression
rlOspfv3IfLinkLSASuppression.reference: OSPF for IPv6, Appendix C.3, Router Interface Parameters
rlOspfv3IfLinkLSASuppression.description: Specifies whether or not link LSA origination is suppressed for broadcast or NBMA interface types. The object is set to value true (1) to suppress the origination.

rlOspfv3IfOperStatus.name: rlOspfv3IfOperStatus
rlOspfv3IfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the OSPF interface.

rlOspfv3IfPassive.name: rlOspfv3IfPassive
rlOspfv3IfPassive.description: Indicates whether this interface is a passive interface. If set to TRUE, we suppress HELLO packets sent on and received from this interface. We will therefore advertise this interface in our LSAs but not run OSPF protocol over it.

rlOspfv3IfLsaRefreshIntvl.name: rlOspfv3IfLsaRefreshIntvl
rlOspfv3IfLsaRefreshIntvl.description: Self-originated LSAs are periodically reflooded into the routing domain, to add to the robustness of the OSPF protocol. This value determines the interval between refreshes of LSAs that are only flooded over this interface, for example type-9 opaque LSAs, and is defaulted to the OSPF standard default of 1800 seconds (30 minutes).

rlOspfv3IfFastHelloMultiplier.name: rlOspfv3IfFastHelloMultiplier
rlOspfv3IfFastHelloMultiplier.description: The number of Hellos that should be sent within 1 second when using Fast Hellos on this interface. This value does not have to be same for all routers attached to a common network, but it is advisable. Fast Hellos are configured using ospfPmIfRtrDeadInterval.

rlOspfv3IfMtuIgnore.name: rlOspfv3IfMtuIgnore
rlOspfv3IfMtuIgnore.description: This object controls whether DC-OSPF checks the MTU size on incoming Database Description packets. By default, if the received MTU size in a DB Description packet is higher than the MTU size configured on the incoming interface, the OSPF adjacency will not be established. If the interface is tunneled over, say, an MPLS network, then the administrator may not know the maximum MTU size and so can tell DC-OSPF to ignore the MTU size on incoming DB description packets.

rlOspfv3IfNameLookup.name: rlOspfv3IfNameLookup
rlOspfv3IfNameLookup.description: A flag to note whether to look up Domain Name System (DNS) names for use in all OSPF show EXEC command displays.

rlOspfv3VirtIfTable.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfTable
rlOspfv3VirtIfTable.reference: OSPF for IPv6, Appendix C.4, Virtual Link Parameters
rlOspfv3VirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual interfaces that the OSPFv3 Process is configured to carry on.

rlOspfv3VirtIfEntry.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfEntry
rlOspfv3VirtIfEntry.description: Information about a single virtual interface. The information in this table is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3VirtIfProcessId.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfProcessId
rlOspfv3VirtIfProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3VirtIfAreaId.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfAreaId
rlOspfv3VirtIfAreaId.description: The transit area that the virtual link traverses. By definition, this is not Area 0.

rlOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor
rlOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the virtual neighbor.

rlOspfv3VirtIfIndex.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfIndex
rlOspfv3VirtIfIndex.description: The local interface index assigned by the OSPFv3 Process to this OSPFv3 virtual interface. It is advertised in Hellos sent over the virtual link and in the router's router-LSAs.

rlOspfv3VirtIfInstId.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfInstId
rlOspfv3VirtIfInstId.description: The local Interface Instance ID assigned by the OSPFv3 Process to this OSPFv3 virtual interface.

rlOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay
rlOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a Link State Update packet over this interface.

rlOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval
rlOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link state advertisement retransmissions for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and Link State Request packets. This value should be well over the expected round-trip time.

rlOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval
rlOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

rlOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval
rlOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before its neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

rlOspfv3VirtIfState.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfState
rlOspfv3VirtIfState.description: OSPF virtual interface states. The same encoding as the ospfV3IfTable is used.

rlOspfv3VirtIfEvents.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfEvents
rlOspfv3VirtIfEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this virtual link. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime.

rlOspfv3VirtIfRowStatus.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfRowStatus
rlOspfv3VirtIfRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction, and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

rlOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount
rlOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Link-scope link state advertisements in this virtual link's link state database.

rlOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum
rlOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Link-scope link state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this virtual link's link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database or to compare the link state database of two routers.

rlOspfv3VirtIfAdminStatus.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfAdminStatus
rlOspfv3VirtIfAdminStatus.description: The desired administrative state of this virtual interface.

rlOspfv3VirtIfOperStatus.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfOperStatus
rlOspfv3VirtIfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of this virtual interface.

rlOspfv3NbrTable.name: rlOspfv3NbrTable
rlOspfv3NbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10, The Neighbor Data Structure
rlOspfv3NbrTable.description: A table describing all neighbors in the locality of the OSPFv3 router.

rlOspfv3NbrEntry.name: rlOspfv3NbrEntry
rlOspfv3NbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10, The Neighbor Data Structure
rlOspfv3NbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single neighbor.

rlOspfv3NbrProcessId.name: rlOspfv3NbrProcessId
rlOspfv3NbrProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3NbrIfIndex.name: rlOspfv3NbrIfIndex
rlOspfv3NbrIfIndex.description: The Local Link ID of the link over which the neighbor can be reached.

rlOspfv3NbrIfInstId.name: rlOspfv3NbrIfInstId
rlOspfv3NbrIfInstId.description: Interface instance over which the neighbor can be reached. This ID has local link significance only.

rlOspfv3NbrRtrId.name: rlOspfv3NbrRtrId
rlOspfv3NbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit unsigned integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

rlOspfv3NbrAddressType.name: rlOspfv3NbrAddressType
rlOspfv3NbrAddressType.description: The address type of rlOspfv3NbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

rlOspfv3NbrAddress.name: rlOspfv3NbrAddress
rlOspfv3NbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address of the neighbor associated with the local link.

rlOspfv3NbrOptions.name: rlOspfv3NbrOptions
rlOspfv3NbrOptions.reference: OSPF for IPv6, Appendix A.2, The Options Field
rlOspfv3NbrOptions.description: A bit mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field.

rlOspfv3NbrPriority.name: rlOspfv3NbrPriority
rlOspfv3NbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designated- router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the Designated Router on this particular network.

rlOspfv3NbrState.name: rlOspfv3NbrState
rlOspfv3NbrState.description: The state of the relationship with this neighbor.

rlOspfv3NbrEvents.name: rlOspfv3NbrEvents
rlOspfv3NbrEvents.description: The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state or an error has occurred. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime.

rlOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen.name: rlOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen
rlOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

rlOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed.name: rlOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed
rlOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor.

rlOspfv3NbrIfId.name: rlOspfv3NbrIfId
rlOspfv3NbrIfId.description: The Interface ID that the neighbor advertises in its Hello packets on this link, that is, the neighbor's local interface index.

rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus.name: rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus
rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a graceful restart helper for the neighbor.

rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge.name: rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge
rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF graceful restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.

rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitReason.name: rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitReason
rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a graceful restart helper for the neighbor. none: no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress: a restart attempt is currently underway. completed: the last restart completed successfully. timedOut: the last restart timed out. topologyChanged: the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.

rlOspfv3NbrDeadTime.name: rlOspfv3NbrDeadTime
rlOspfv3NbrDeadTime.description: The time remaining in seconds within which we need to receive a hello packet from the neighbor or we declare the adjacency down. If fast hellos area in use, this value is always set to 1. If the oper_status is down or ospfPmNbrState is DOWN, then the value is set to zero and the field is not valid.

rlOspfv3NbrAreaId.name: rlOspfv3NbrAreaId
rlOspfv3NbrAreaId.description: The area to which the neighbor belongs. If the oper_status is down, then this value is set to zero and the field is not valid.

rlOspfv3CfgNbrTable.name: rlOspfv3CfgNbrTable
rlOspfv3CfgNbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10, The Neighbor Data Structure
rlOspfv3CfgNbrTable.description: A table describing all configured neighbors. The Configured Neighbors table just gives OSPFv3 information for sending OSPFv3 packets to potential neighbors and is typically used on NBMA and Point-to-Multipoint networks. Once a Hello is received from a neighbor in the Configured Neighbor table, an entry for that neighbor is created in the Neighbor table and adjacency state is maintained there. Neighbors on multi-access or Point-to-Point networks can use multicast addressing, so only Neighbor table entries are created for them.

rlOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.name: rlOspfv3CfgNbrEntry
rlOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10, The Neighbor Data Structure
rlOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single configured neighbor. The information in this table is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspf3CfgNbrProcessId.name: rlOspf3CfgNbrProcessId
rlOspf3CfgNbrProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex.name: rlOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex
rlOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex.description: The Local Link ID of the link over which the neighbor can be reached.

rlOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId.name: rlOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId
rlOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId.description: Interface instance over which the neighbor can be reached. This ID has local link significance only.

rlOspfv3CfgNbrAddressType.name: rlOspfv3CfgNbrAddressType
rlOspfv3CfgNbrAddressType.description: The address type of rlOspfv3NbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

rlOspfv3CfgNbrAddress.name: rlOspfv3CfgNbrAddress
rlOspfv3CfgNbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address of the neighbor associated with the local link.

rlOspfv3CfgNbrPriority.name: rlOspfv3CfgNbrPriority
rlOspfv3CfgNbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designated- router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the Designated Router on this particular network.

rlOspfv3CfgNbrRowStatus.name: rlOspfv3CfgNbrRowStatus
rlOspfv3CfgNbrRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction, and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrTable.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrTable
rlOspfv3VirtNbrTable.description: A table describing all virtual neighbors.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrProcessId.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrProcessId
rlOspfv3VirtNbrProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId
rlOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex
rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex.description: The local Interface ID for the virtual link over which the neighbor can be reached.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId
rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId.description: The interface instance for the virtual link over which the neighbor can be reached.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType
rlOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType.description: The address type of rlOspfv3VirtNbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrAddress.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrAddress
rlOspfv3VirtNbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address advertised by this virtual neighbor. It must be a global scope address.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrOptions
rlOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.reference: OSPF for IPv6, Appendix A.2, The Options Field
rlOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.description: A bit mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrState.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrState
rlOspfv3VirtNbrState.description: The state of the virtual neighbor relationship.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrEvents.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrEvents
rlOspfv3VirtNbrEvents.description: The number of times this virtual link has changed its state or an error has occurred. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of rlOspfv3DiscontinuityTime.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen
rlOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed
rlOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfId.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfId
rlOspfv3VirtNbrIfId.description: The Interface ID that the neighbor advertises in its Hello packets on this virtual link, that is, the neighbor's local Interface ID.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus
rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a graceful restart helper for the neighbor.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge
rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in the current OSPF graceful restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitReason.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitReason
rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a graceful restart helper for the neighbor. none: no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress: a restart attempt is currently underway. completed: the last restart completed successfully. timedOut: the last restart timed out. topologyChanged: the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrDeadTime.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrDeadTime
rlOspfv3VirtNbrDeadTime.description: The time remaining in seconds within which we need to receive a hello packet from the neighbor or we declare the adjacency down. If fast hellos area in use, this value is always set to 1. If the oper_status is down or ospfPmVirtNbrState is DOWN, then the value is set to zero and the field is not valid.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregateTable.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregateTable
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateTable.description: The Area Aggregate Table acts as an adjunct to the Area Table. It describes those address aggregates that are configured to be propagated from an area. Its purpose is to reduce the amount of information that is known beyond an area's borders. A range of IPv6 prefixes specified by a prefix / prefix length pair. Note that if ranges are configured such that one range subsumes another range, the most specific match is the preferred one.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2, Area parameters
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.description: A single area aggregate entry. Information in this table is persistent, and when this object is written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregateProcessId.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregateProcessId
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2, Area parameters
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaID.description: The area the Address Aggregate is to be found within.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1, The LSA header
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.description: The type of the Address Aggregate. This field specifies the Area LSDB type that this Address Aggregate applies to.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType
rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType.description: The prefix type of rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix. Only IPv6 addresses are expected.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix
rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2, Area parameters

rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength
rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2, Area parameters
rlOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits). A prefix can not be shorter than 3 bits.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregateRowStatus.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregateRowStatus
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction, and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect.description: Prefixes subsumed by ranges will either trigger the advertisement of the indicated aggregate (advertiseMatching) or result in the prefix not being advertised at all outside the area.

rlOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag.name: rlOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag
rlOspfv3AreaAggregateRouteTag.description: This tag is advertised only in the summarized As-External LSA when summarizing from NSSA-LSAs to AS-External-LSAs.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbTable.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbTable
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Link-scope LSDB for virtual interfaces. The LSDB contains the Link-scope link state advertisements from virtual interfaces.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbEntry.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbEntry
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbEntry.description: A single Link-scope link state advertisement for a virtual interface.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbProcessId.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbProcessId
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbIfAreaId.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbIfAreaId
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbIfAreaId.description: The transit area that the virtual link traverses. By definition, this is not Area 0.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbIfNeighbor.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbIfNeighbor
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the virtual neighbor.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbType.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbType
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. Link-scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbRouterId.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbRouterId
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1, Global parameters
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbLsid.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbLsid
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS type-specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbSequence.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbSequence
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6, LS sequence number
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number, the more recent the advertisement.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbAge.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbAge
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbAge.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.1, LS age; Extending OSPF to Support Demand Circuits, Section 2.2, The LS age field.
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds. The high-order bit of the LS age field is considered the DoNotAge bit for support of on-demand circuits.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbChecksum.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbChecksum
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbAdvertisement.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbAdvertisement
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire link state advertisement, including its header.

rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbTypeKnown.name: rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbTypeKnown
rlOspfv3VirtLinkLsdbTypeKnown.description: The value true (1) indicates that the LSA type is recognized by this router.

rlOspfv3ConfigErrorType.name: rlOspfv3ConfigErrorType
rlOspfv3ConfigErrorType.description: Potential types of configuration conflicts. Used by the rlOspfv3ConfigError and rlOspfv3ConfigVirtError notifications.

rlOspfv3PacketSrc.name: rlOspfv3PacketSrc
rlOspfv3PacketSrc.description: The IPv6 address of an inbound packet that cannot be identified by a neighbor instance. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.

rlOspfv3VirtIfStateChange.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfStateChange
rlOspfv3VirtIfStateChange.description: An rlOspfv3VirtIfStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPFv3 virtual interface. This notification should be generated when the interface state regresses (e.g., goes from Point-to-Point to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point).

rlOspfv3NbrStateChange.name: rlOspfv3NbrStateChange
rlOspfv3NbrStateChange.description: An rlOspfv3NbrStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non-virtual OSPFv3 neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., 2-Way or Full). When a neighbor transitions from or to Full on non-broadcast multi-access and broadcast networks, the notification should be generated by the Designated Router. A Designated Router transitioning to Down will be noted by ospfIfStateChange.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange
rlOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange.description: An rlOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPFv3 virtual neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., Full).

rlOspfv3IfConfigError.name: rlOspfv3IfConfigError
rlOspfv3IfConfigError.description: An rlOspfv3IfConfigError notification signifies that a packet has been received on a non-virtual interface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's configuration parameters. Note that the event optionMismatch should cause a notification only if it prevents an adjacency from forming.

rlOspfv3VirtIfConfigError.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfConfigError
rlOspfv3VirtIfConfigError.description: An rlOspfv3VirtIfConfigError notification signifies that a packet has been received on a virtual interface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's configuration parameters. Note that the event optionMismatch should cause a notification only if it prevents an adjacency from forming.

rlOspfv3IfRxBadPacket.name: rlOspfv3IfRxBadPacket
rlOspfv3IfRxBadPacket.description: An rlOspfv3IfRxBadPacket notification signifies that an OSPFv3 packet that cannot be parsed has been received on a non-virtual interface.

rlOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket.name: rlOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket
rlOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket.description: An rlOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket notification signifies that an OSPFv3 packet that cannot be parsed has been received on a virtual interface.

rlOspfv3LsdbOverflow.name: rlOspfv3LsdbOverflow
rlOspfv3LsdbOverflow.description: An rlOspfv3LsdbOverflow notification signifies that the number of LSAs in the router's link state database has exceeded rlOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.

rlOspfv3LsdbApproachingOverflow.name: rlOspfv3LsdbApproachingOverflow
rlOspfv3LsdbApproachingOverflow.description: An rlOspfv3LsdbApproachingOverflow notification signifies that the number of LSAs in the router's link state database has exceeded ninety percent of rlOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.

rlOspfv3IfStateChange.name: rlOspfv3IfStateChange
rlOspfv3IfStateChange.description: An rlOspfv3IfStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non-virtual OSPFv3 interface. This notification should be generated when the interface state regresses (e.g., goes from DR to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point, DR Other, DR, or Backup).

rlOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange.name: rlOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange
rlOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange.description: An rlOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange notification indicates that there has been a change in the router's ability to translate OSPFv3 NSSA LSAs into OSPFv3 External LSAs. This notification should be generated when the Translator Status transitions from or to any defined status on a per-area basis.

rlOspfv3RestartStatusChange.name: rlOspfv3RestartStatusChange
rlOspfv3RestartStatusChange.description: An rlOspfv3RestartStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart state for the router. This notification should be generated when the router restart status changes.

rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange.name: rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange
rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange.description: An rlOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart helper state for the neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor restart helper status transitions for a neighbor.

rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange.name: rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange
rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange.description: An rlOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart helper state for the virtual neighbor. This notification should be generated when the virtual neighbor restart helper status transitions for a virtual neighbor.

rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfEvents.name: rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfEvents
rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfEvents.description: A bit mask indicating enable SNMP notifications for OSPF errors. Bit 0, if set, for authenticationFailure trap. enables only the ospfIfFailure trap. Allows SNMP notifications to be sent when a packet has been received on a nonvirtual interface from a neighbor router whose authentication key or authentication type conflicts with the authentication key or authentication type of this router. Bit 1, if set, for badPacket trap. enables only the ospfIfRxBadPacket trap. Allows SNMP notifications to be sent when an OSPF packet that has not been parsed has been received on a nonvirtual interface. Bit 2, if set, for configError trap. enables only the ospfIfConfigError trap. Sends SNMP notifications when a packet has been received in a nonvirtual interface from a neighbor router whose configuration parameters conflict with the configuration parameters of this router. Bit 3, if set, for virtAuthenticationFailure trap. enables only the ospfVirtIfFailure trap. Allows SNMP notifications to be sent when a packet has been received on a virtual interface from a neighbor router whose authentication key or authentication type conflicts with the authentication key or authentication type of this router. Bit 4, if set, for virtBadPacket trap. enables only the ospfVirtIfRxBadPacket trap. Allows SNMP notifications to be sent when an OSPF packet that has not been parsed has been received on a virtual interface. Bit 5, if set, for virtConfigError trap. enables only the ospfVirtIfConfigError trap. Sends SNMP notifications when a packet has been received in a virtual interface from a neighbor router whose configuration parameters conflict with the configuration parameters of this router.

rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfRateLimit.name: rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfRateLimitSeconds
rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfRateLimit.description: Sets the rate limit window size, in seconds. A number from 2 to 60. The default value is 10.

rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfRateLimit.name: rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfRateLimitTrapNumber
rlOspfv3EnableNotificationsOspfRateLimit.description: Sets the maximum number of traps sent during the window time. A number from 0 to 300. The default number is 7.
